{
  "texts": [
    "In these figures, the stacked bar charts display the distribution (proportion) of user responses, color-coded to represent different answer categories.",
    "In order to facilitate interpretation, each bar is aligned around the neutral answer (neither agree nor disagree) which is marked by a vertical line.",
    "This alignment serves as a reference point, allowing for easy identification of negative responses (ranging from strongly disagree to somewhat disagree) and positive responses (ranging from somewhat agree to strongly agree).",
    "Table 4 shows the averages and standard deviations of the scores for the questions",
